Responsibilities:
Deep-Dive Exploration: Conducting thorough exploratory data analysis to identify underlying
patterns, anomalies, and relationships within complex data sets.
Hypothesis Generation: Developing hypotheses based on initial data exploration to explain business
outcomes.
Scientific Validation: Designing experiments to collect additional data and validate these hypotheses
when required.
Insight Communication: Preparing and presenting comprehensive EDA reports to stakeholders,
highlighting significant findings and strategic recommendations.

Skills Required:
Analytical Mindset: Exceptional ability to organize and interpret large sets of data to discern patterns
and derive meaningful insights relevant to the business.
Business Intelligence Synthesis: Ability to gather insights into clear, "CXO-ready" summaries that
highlight strategic recommendations rather than just technical metrics.
SQL Mastery: Intermediate to advanced skills in SQL are necessary for effective data extraction and
exploration. Exceptional ability to write complex, performant queries to extract data varied sources
and data environments.

Statistical Proficiency: Intermediate to advanced proficiency in statistics and statistical tools to
summarize key findings accurately.
Analytical Engineering (Python/Polars): High proficiency in using Python (specifically Polars or
Pandas) for data manipulation. You prefer code-based solutions over manual spreadsheets for
scalability and reproducibility.
Modern Data Stack Familiarity: Experience working with (or a strong desire to learn) Apache
Iceberg, DuckDB, and PySpark for managing large-scale data analysis.
Linux Familiarity: Comfortable working in a Linux environment via terminal/SSH to manage Python
environments and background services.
Nice to Have:
Statistical Modelling: Familiarity with time series analysis, cohort analysis, cluster analysis, or
simulations.
Ad-Tech Knowledge: Familiarity with the structure of Amazon Advertising reports and keyword
match-type competition.
Automation: Experience with basic CI/CD or automation scripts to keep data pipelines and apps
updated without manual intervention.
Machine Learning: Experience in building and implementing ML models or Decision Support
Systems.
Advanced Analytics: Exposure to text analytics, NLP, or LLM/RAG application development

